			the latest web standards.
			<a href="http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=245151">Learn more…</a>
		 -->
	</li>

	<li class="two">
		<h5>Ingredients</h5>
		Whether you are talking about ingredients in a food you eat or in your medications, ingredients may play an important role in your battle with migraines.
		There are two benefits to keeping track of items at this level:
		<ul style="list-style:initial; list-style-position:initial">
			<li>You can see over time if a certain allergy or food ingredient is triggering your migraines.</li>
			<li>You can see over time how effective certain ingredients in your medications are against your migraine attacks.</li>
		</ul>
		<!--
		<h5>Add NuGet packages and jump-start your coding</h5>
		NuGet makes it easy to install and update free libraries and tools.
        <a href="http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=245153">Learn more…</a>
			-->
	</li>

	<li class="three">
		<h5>Symmptoms</h5>
		Let's face it; if migraines were just a simple headache, there wouldn't be very much to complain about. 
		However, migraines are not just pain in the head, they might include things like:
		<ul style="list-style:initial; list-style-position:initial">
			<li>Nausea</li>
			<li>Vomiting</li>
			<li>Intense sensitivity to lights</li>
			<li>Intense sensitivity to sounds</li>
			<li>Intense sensitivity to scents</li>
			<li>Fatigue</li>
			<li>Weakness</li>
			<li>Crankiness</li>
			<li>Depression</li>
			<li>Inability to focus or complete tasks</li>
			<li>Sudden change in vision</li>
			<li>And much more...</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ol>

<h3>We are currently working on:</h3>
<ol class="round">
	<li class="one">
		<h5>Diary Entries</h5>
		Currently, we are working on making it possible to make diary entries. Most of the groundwork has been paved.
	</li>
</ol>

<h3>We are in the process of adding the next few items in the near future:</h3>
<ol class="round">
	<li class="one">
		<h5>Intensity</h5>
		Doctors will always ask what the intensity of your pain is on a 1-10 scale, but sometimes it's not just intensity of the pain that is of concern. 
		We'll cover things like:
		<ul style="list-style:initial; list-style-position:initial">
			<li>Pain</li>
			<li>Nausea</li>
			<li>Custom intensities for symptoms that have the greatest effect on your day to day life...</li>
		</ul>
	</li>

	<li class="two">
		<h5>Location of pain on the head</h5>
		Migraines can happen the same way and area of the head or they can change. 
		This little tidbit of information might just prove interesting to you, yet it could be useful information for your doctor.
	</li>

	<li class="three">
		<h5>Triggers</h5>
		Ultimately, there are two kinds of triggers that this diary is aware of: "potential triggers" and "known triggers". These triggers could include items such as:
		<ul style="list-style:initial; list-style-position:initial">
			<li>Weather</li>
			<li>Food/Ingredients</li>
			<li>Stressful incedents/environments</li>
			<li>Lack of sleep</li>
			<li>Bright lights</li>
			<li>Loud sounds</li>
			<li>Strong scents</li>
			<li>Dehydration or hunger</li>
			<li>And more...</li>
		</ul>
