			-->
	</li>

	<li class="four">
		<h5>Comments</h5>
		You'll also be able to make comments on each of your migraine diary entries. This means that if there's anything this app doesn't cover, you will still be covered. 
		Who knows, maybe sometime in the future, some of those common comments might become features to this diary. 
		In that case, if you jotted them down, you'll have no problem recalling them at a later time...
	</li>

	<li class="five">
		<h5>Email and exporting to Excel</h5>
		This whole app is great and all, but what good would it do if you couldn't hand a report to your doctor or have a spreadsheet to analyze in your own time?
		Eventually, we plan on having both of those features added for your convenience.
	</li>

	<li class="six">
		<h5>Charts and Statistical Data</h5>
		Once the basics are down, we can dive in and give you new ways to view your diary:
		<ul style="list-style:initial; list-style-position:initial">
			<li>Which months or even days of the week were you most prone to migraines?</li>
			<li>What was the weather like when you were fighting off all of your migraine attacks?</li>
			<li>Which foods/ingredients seem to be eaten more around the time of a migraine?</li>
			<li>Which potential triggers are actually triggers?</li>
			<li>And the possibilities are endless...</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ol>
